<body><p>GE.13-17610 
</p>
<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twenty-fourth session 
</b></p>
<p>Agenda item 3 
</p>
<p><b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
</b></p>
<p><b>political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
</b></p>
<p><b>including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Algeria</b>*<b>, Cuba</b>*<b>, Egypt</b>*<b>, Ethiopia, India, Pakistan, Saudi Arabia</b>*<b>, South Africa</b>*<b>, 
</b></p>
<p><b>Uganda, Venezuela (Bolivarian Republic of): amendment to draft resolution 
</b></p>
<p><b>A/HRC/24/L.24 
</b></p>
<p><b>  24</b>/&#8230;<b> Civil society space: creating and maintaining, in law  
 and in practice, a safe and enabling environment 
</b></p>
<p>Paragraph 1 <i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p><i>Reminds </i>States of their obligation to respect and fully protect the civil, political, 
</p>
<p>economic, social and cultural rights of all individuals to, inter alia, freedom of peaceful 
</p>
<p>assembly, association, opinion and expression, online as well as offline, including for 
</p>
<p>persons espousing minority or dissenting views or beliefs, as well as the right to 
</p>
<p>development, and that respect for all such rights, in relation to civil society, contributes to 
</p>
<p>addressing and resolving challenges and issues that are important to society,  
</p>
<p>    
</p>
<p>  
 
</p>
<p>* Non-member State of the Human Rights Council. 
</p>
